values:
Graduated from JMU =(  It's so depressing that I'm done with college.  I'm definitely going to miss JMU and all the great people there.  It makes me sad everytime I think about it.  At least David and Diana are going to continue the legacy at JMU.

Now I'm going to bum around NOVA until Deloitte lets me start working in August.  The two weeks of training in the ATL should be fun.  Living at home is going to be different, but I'm glad my parents are cool with everything.  

Kim and I got a really cute bunny.  It's a lionhead mix and it's awesome.  It has a cool mane and sorta acts like a puppy.  Here are a couple pictures of him: http://community.webshots.com/user/beebeth His black fur is hard to show up in pictures so they don't do a lot of justice for him.  We named him Duke and I think it's suiting him really well.

Well thats it for now.

So Spring Break was kick ass.  Miami, Nassau, CocoCay, & Key West were the great places we visited on our cruise.  Nassau was kinda trashy and people kept trying to sell us weed.  But the white sand/clear water beaches in Nassau and CocoCay were amazing.  I had a great time with everyone and ate really well.  I'm definitely going on another cruise in the future.

So I've been back in the burg for 2 days now.  Kinda depressing that we gotta get back to the school routine.  Two more months till graduation, I'm sure that's going to fly by and I'm going to wish that it wasn't time to move on to a different phase in our lives.  I am excited about starting and working for Deloitte, I just hope that I get to start earlier than august.

All right, here are some pics from spring break

http://community.webshots.com/user/shyuperman2

Enjoy...

Man, Kim is the coolest girl ever. I freakin love her so much! I want to marry her and have little 1/2 asian babies with her! YEAH!

**note, Dan didn't write this entry

I got an offer from Deloitte!

other than that... senior year has been busy as hell....

herro...

It's already thanksgiving... kinda wondering where did this whole semester go.  I have to say this semester has been the hardest semester in my college career.  I'm definitely a different person.  So instead of bitching about the stress I've gone through, I'll sum everything up with how are things now:

Brother of Alpha Kappa Psi
Finished my business plan
Doing well in school
Assholes need to stop hitting my car 
Gotta get my job back at sports authority for break

All of the stress/break downs/work so far has been worth it.  I've battled through them and benefited from everything.  Next semester is going to be different and I don't know how I'm going to handle it.  Just gotta keep on trucking...

So now I have to make my finals my bitch and have the best last two weeks of this semester.

So we had our first official intramural basketball game last night.  And three minutes into the game, I fracture my ankle by landing wrong after getting a rebound.  I was in the hospital for about one hour, I was surprised how fast it went.  Fortunately, I had Jo with me and she was the one that took me to the hospital and situated back at my dorm.  So on my discharge sheet is says "There is a small chip fracture in your ankle.  This fracture was caused by stretching the joint ligaments, which pulled off a small piece of bone."  Final diagnosis: Acute flake fracture right talus.  So the doc says it's a 6 week injury.  I got crutches, an ace wrap, and an ankle stirrup splint.  So he said I should be on crutches for about two weeks and hopefully be able to walk around then.  

So I probably won't be able to play anymore games in this intramural season.  I'll be lucky if I could do anything atheletic for the next month.  So that sucks... it's just totally different going around campus on crutches.  And apparently a lot of other people are on crutches too, I think most of them are basketball related too.  So these next few weeks should be interesting...

Time really flies.  Fall semester is already over and I'm back at home.  It's been a whole semester since my last update.  The past semester was glorious, a lot of great times and memories.  So finals week was fun, I had 3 8ams and an exam on Sunday.  Had exams in all of my classes.  But I am glad to be done and at home.  Being a business major is kinda different from CS.  I enjoy it a lot better and it's more to my liking, but it is difficult as well.  5 business courses next semester so I'll be living at Showker.  So having Matthias as a roommate has been pretty fun.  We started a lot of random competitive games and just lots of fun.  It's official we're living at The Commons next year... 891J.  It's going to be great with Justin, Matthias, and Kyle.  The most diverse apartment you'll see.  Even though we got screwed over by Sunchase we got a pretty decent apartment.  

So this break is going to consist of me working at Sports Authority and relaxing.  I did work at Sports Authority during Thanksgiving break, I worked most of break so then I could keep myself busy.  This break should be interesting, hopefully I'll be able to see people from JMU and have some fun.

hello there... welcome to my LJ...  I guess I haven't felt the urge to update this thing... maybe it's because I've been busy or just lazy.  Well summer is almost coming to an end.  Everything seems to go by really fast.  My life has been taken up by work.  Rec-Pac is great... I really enjoy working there.  I just wish it was longer than 6 weeks.  This week will be the last week.  I'm going to miss my co workers and the kids... they're great.  Working at Rec-Pac has it's advantages and disadvantages, but this year has made me really consider about doing it again next summer.  Hopefully it'll still be the same staff because I doubt it'll be as fun next year without them.  I'm going to miss the parties, bashing the kids, Starbucks, Zebra cakes, PIG, Andy, and everything else.  

On Saturday, the Liu's and Shyu's will be going to Disney World.  It's going to be fun, we're going to be there for 5 days, 4 nights.  It should be a lot of fun without parents.  I guess that'll be the highlight of my summer.  After we get back, I'll probably just enjoy my time before the semester starts again.

Speaking of school, at first I didn't really want to go back.  I got used of working and staying home that I didn't want to go back... I adapt pretty easily... and I guess I'll do the same once I get back to JMU.  However after some events that happened this week I want to go back.  I swap classes so the earliest I have to wake up is 9:30 am on tuesday and Thursday.  My schedule is a lot like last semesters.  I only have one friday class... and my first class on Monday Wednesday and Friday is at 12:20.  So it's going to be fun... except I don't finish until 6:30 on tuesdays and thursdays.  Since I switched majors, I really don't know what to expect with my classes.  Hopefully all of my business classes will be like GBUS.  I was kinda worried because I felt as if I was going through freshman year all over again.  New classes... having to deal with a roommie.. and being uncertain.  Well it also all changed after I found out that Matthias and I got moved to Potomac.  I was really happy after I found out because Potomac has A/C and I'm back at the Skyline area.  It's going to be sweet because a lot of my friends and old hallmates will be at C'peake... and a new Super Walmart openned up near the Skyline area.  Now I'm really excited about going back...

All right I'm out of stuff to talk about... I'll update once I get back to school... enjoy the rest of your summer..

Heres a post to make my handful of LJ readers happy.  Well recently I have been doing training for REC-PAC.  Tomorrow will be my last day of training, but tomorrow is more like a site set up day.  So far we have been attending workshops for the different situations and activities we're going to do in the camp.  It was kinda boring at times, but overall it was pretty fun.  There are a lot of great camp leaders and directors.  The McNair staff is pretty cool, I have a cool site director and three awesome camp leaders.  REC-PAC actually starts next Monday, which is going to be tight and I guess choatic since it's my first year doing it.  I'm going to have fun getting paid playing games and doing crafts with kids.  I definitely love how the government works because I'm getting paid 25.5hours this week, but we only worked like 20 hours (paid training).  Had training workshops with Justin and Alex Schad (sp?).

Well last week was kinda my off week and prep days for the start of rec-pac.  I worked a week for Shanif.  We painted and power washed a house.  It was fun and kinda difficult.  It a different type of working experience compared to a desk job.  It's sure better than applied technologies.  So thats pretty much the highlight of this month.  Just been up to with the usual stuff... chilling with friends, video games, and stuff.  I'm glad it just  stopped raining.  I guess I don't mind the hot weather... better than rain.  Well this is a pretty short entry.  I hope everyone's summer is going well.  Take care

I guess I should write an entry.  Well it's been more than a month since I've last posted.  I'm glad to see that I get more comments when I post random stuff on my LJ.  For your information: Russell Wong is cool, I found out that he a main character on a WB show.  It's sorta like a teenage kung fu mystery series.  It's interesting... it teaches some Chinese stuff.... I will be surprised if the show goes the whole summer season.

Well I've been home for over 3 weeks now.  I quickly adopted back to the home life.  I do miss all my friends and things to do back at JMU.  But it's really nice to sleep as long as I want and sit on my ass and do nothing.  Well I got a job at RECPAC, but that doesn't start until late June.  So I've decided to apply for the movie theatre.  The hours there are pretty flexible and I guess I'll try taking on two jobs once recpac starts, but I'll just quit once it becomes too much.  So... I might just end up working two weeks and giving my two weeks notice =P.  Well so far summer break has been uneventful.  I've been hanging out with friends/family, playing sports/video games, and I went to Mike's graduation earlier this month.  I got to visit good old Blacksburg again... JMU's football team will be paying them a visit next season... we're definitely going to get raped.  

Justin and I got memberships at Olympus gym, so hopefully I'll be able to continue with my lifting routine and get off my butt.  Yeah... so basically my summer is going to be made up of working... chilling... and other stuff.  It's going to be sweet in August because Mike, Alice, my sister and I are going to Disney World for 5 days.  It's going to be great with the four of us.  So I really don't have much to say.  I'm surprised I wrote this much.  Well I guess I'll write again in a month.  Have a good summer for those who are already out.  Good luck and enjoy May/Summer Session (Nelly/Jess)

click here to find out which asian action superstar you are!
You are Russell Wong. you like to act tough and be bad, but you are often sensitive to the needs of others as well as
the needs of your peers. ur the dainty, delictable, and sensitive type. u like to be pampered and treated
like the queen that u are!

yeah... you'll rarely see me update my LJ more than once a month... but I thought this quiz was pretty cool and LJ material... hmm... But I thought Russell Wong was pretty tight in Romeo Must Die...

Happy belated Easter, I hope everyone had a good one.  Well I finally decided to get off my lazy ass and update this thing.  Of course, a lot of things have happened since I've last updated, I guess I'll just talk about things that I can remember.  So I went home this weekend, it was nice because my professor cancelled class on friday, so I was able to go home with Mike on Thursday.  The weekend wasn't too bad.  I spent a lot of time with my friends and after hanging out with alice and linda, I know their latest gossip.  It was nice to hang out with my family.  I talked to my parents and it looks like I'm getting the camry at the end of my 2nd year.  I probably won't have enough money saved up by the start of my 3rd year to pay for a new car.  So I decided to drive around the cam and buy a better car once I get out of college.  Wow, I can't believe I have three more weeks of school.  I'm really not looking back in going back home.  JMU is a lot of fun, I just want to stay here and do nothing.  As of right now, I do not have a job lined up.  I really need a job for the summer, if I don't get a good one, I guess I'll apply for a job at the mall.  Money is money... and I need it for summer.

Well as with school, things are setting down now.  No more hell weeks, just getting ready for finals and all.  Matthias and I are going to room together next year.  It's going to be tight, for right now we're at Chandler Hall, hopefully we'll be able to go back to C'peake or Potomac.  It would be nice to have A/C but Chandler is fine with me, since 4 out of my 5 classes will be near Chandler.  Yup, I've decided to change majors.... changing to CIS.  CS didn't go to waste, I get credit for taking CS 139 and 239.  It should be fun rooming with Matthias, it's going to be different, but nothing I can't get used to.  He'll be bring down his mustang, and he said he'll teach me how to drive stick(this will be my 2nd attempt to learn since I wasn't able to practice because brandon sold his celica).  So as for the rooming situation, I'm looking forward in it.  Can't believe I'm almost done with my 1st year... crazy.  Going to miss all my JMU friends and all.

As for summer, I don't really have big plans.  Hopefully I'll be working, but the Liu's and the Shyu's are planning a trip to Disney World.  It should be a lot of fun with just us 4... no parents... 5 days... =D  Well I'm done... I'll write again in a month....

Wow... spring break is finally here.  It's been a hell of a week and I'm just glad that it's finally done.  The week before spring break is pretty much a hell week for many people.  I had 2 papers, 1 quiz, 1 midterm, 2 labs, and 1 program due this week.  Everything other than CS work wasn't really too bad.  The program was the bitch, it took me forever and I didn't even finish.  A weeks worth of code in 40+ pages and it wasn't even completed.  I dunno... CS is a lot of work and the way that things are going I might not be accepted as a CS major.  With the way my professor teaches and grades, I would be lucky with a C in CS239.  My grades are pretty poor right now, I think my highest grades are in Calc and GWrit102... In some of my classes, I didn't do so well on the tests and so far they have been my own grades.  I'm definitely going to work a lot harder and study a lot harder once I get back from break.  I actually have a good amount of hw to do during break... so I'm going to be a nerd and do it during break.  So yeah, after not being able to complete the program, Joe and I talked about the possiblity of changing majors next semester.  It's kinda scary because we aren't sure what else we would like to major in.  I wouldn't mind majoring in CIS but I have a feeling it's a BS major.  I really don't mine CS... the programming is hard, but I can do it... but the way my professor is currently teaching and grading I won't have the GPA to make it in.  So yeah... this first half of the semester has been a wake up call for me.

Well I'm kinda glad that I'm home.  Time really flies when you're in college.  I can't believe we've already gone through 7 some weeks of classes.  I am glad that I get to relax and just enjoy a week somewhat off.  It just sucked that our spring break is after UVA/Tech's.  I really don't have anything planned for spring break.  I'm probably just going to bum around at home.

Well other than my hell weeks and all the work I've been doing, I've been trying to have fun while I can.  We went to Madison Grill on Wednesday for Justin's Birthday.  It was pretty fun, I got Justin a JMU shot glass and I hope he puts it into good use by taking shots of OJ =P  Last weekend we went out for my birthday.  Basically just chilled and had fun on friday and saturday.  It was a lot of fun and I have to thank all of you guys.  I've realized that a lot of people are born in Feburary or March, it's kinda crazy.  So other than my academic life, I'm doing great.  Playing intramural softball with friends once we get back from break.  Some of the rules are kinda gay, but it should be fun.  

Well this was suppose to be a short entry, but it turned out to be pretty lengthy.  I think I'll stop here... can't really think of what else to say.  For those people who's breaks are coming to a close: I hope everyone had a good break and those people who's breaks are just beginning: I hope everyone has a safe and fun break.  Take it easy... good night

It's been a really long time since I've posted a LJ.  Last time I posted was at the start of this semester.  So yeah... back at college... getting close to the middle of the semester.  Classes are more difficult now, but I'm getting used to it.  I got over bitching about the classes, I just want to get this semester over with.  So this weekend has been pretty cool.  Kristen came to JMU for the weekend, but ended up going back to UVA due to the snow storm and her sickness.  It was a lot of fun hanging out with her and everyone else.  We ended up doing a lot of fun things.

So we had our first blizzard of the year.  It snowed a lot here, but it was nothing compared to what people got back in northern virginia.  It has been really great walking around campus in the snow.  It's just amazing to look at the landscape around campus and how cool snow makes things look.  We didn't have classes today and we're not going to have any tomorrow.  A four day weekend, it's great... but going back to class on Wednesday is going to be horrible.  I'm currently done with 2 out of my 3, back to back hell weeks.  I have a psych and cs test this week.  So those should be interesting.  Tomorrow is going to be a big study day I guess, it's good that I got some homework done on Sunday.  So life back at college has been pretty good.  Life outside of class has been pretty great.  Just trying to enjoy it as much as I can.  But sometimes I feel like something is missing, but I don't know what it is.

Spring break starts the 2nd week of March.  I don't know what I'm going to do, I was thinking about chilling with hallmates at virginia beach and p-town, but I doubt my parents are going to let me drive down there.  Spring break really isn't far away.  I'm really surprised that time is going by so fast here.  Sunday was my mom's birthday and my birthday is like two weeks away.  I wasn't even aware of it until Megan brought it up.  I dunno... it's just weird... I've changed in a way... it's cool that my birthday is coming up, but I'm not really excited about it.  Maybe I'm just getting old or something... This year I don't really want anything... just like what happened for Xmas and all.  So yeah... just rambling random thoughts.  Sometimes I don't even know what I want anymore... maybe it's because I currently have all I need and I don't need anything.  I've gotten so much into a routine now.  The same routine of going to classes... coming back and doing hw... enjoying life... dunno... just weird I guess.  

I say "weird" and "dunno" a lot in my LJ posts.  And I continue to spit out random thoughts.  If anyone is interested, download some music from Niki Barr.  Pretty good artist, attended JMU for a year then left to pursue her singing career.  I saw her in concert here at JMU with Brian.  Music isn't too bad... she's sorta like  Michelle Branch.  So yeah... intramural basketball... we should call ourselves the "touchables" because we weren't really untouchable during the season.  1-4... and our only win was from a forefit.  Playoffs start thursday, hopefully we'll advance... but whatever, it was fun while it lasted.  I am going to do intramural basketball again next year.  It's also cool that I'm "coaching" Megan's intramural team.  Her team is pretty cool, with a lot of talent.  And fun just to hang out with friends and watch a game.  Probably going to play intramural softball with everyone later this semester.  It should be a lot of fun.  So yeah... I hope everyone is doing well.  Enjoy the snow and have fun.  Off to shower... I guess I'll post again in a month =P

Wow, look how fast a month can go by... =(  I'll be leaving for JMU in like 10 hours.  Unfortuantely, I've gotten used to home and I don't want to go back to school.  I wanna go back to JMU for the college life, but not for the classes.  I am not looking forward to my classes...  My first class is at 11am on Monday, which isn't too bad.  But I got 15mins to get from one side of campus to the other...  I wish they could've given us more time to get settled back into college before classes start.  

Well overall winter break was fun.  It was nice to go back to work and make some extra money.  I hope I find a better job for summer.  Hanging out with everyone was very enjoyable... a lot of new memories... (nuhuhuhuhuh =P)  I guess the only down fall to break was getting my wisdom teeth pulled.  I got all 4 pulled on Monday.  It wasn't that painful, but the swelling sucked.  Eating crappy food for a couple days got frustrating.  But things are good now, just gotta clean out my mouth with this water gun they gave me...  

Eric had a get together today.  It was a lot of fun, Eric's house has a lot of goodies...  Played darts and all... pretty fun.  It was nice to see everyone for the final time for a couple of months.  I guess I have only spring break to look foward to.  If anyone wants to come down to JMU, IM me or call me up.  Right now, it feels like I'm going to college for the first time again... It's kinda weird.  Well I guess this is it... I guess I better start packing, like everyone else.  I hope everyone has a good spring semester/2nd quarter.  Take it easy...

Hmm... what day is today?  Tuesday?  I guess I'm breaking my normal routine of updating my LJ every 3 weeks at home.  Right now nothing is really going on.  Woke up an hour ago and I've been working on my GCOM speech.  I wanted to do my speech on traffic accidents, but I didn't have enough information.  So I decided to do it on sleep.  It interested me in Psych last year, so I thought it would be a nice topic.  But I don't know what to focus my speech on, I have all this information... I guess I'll speak about how we deal with sleep or something.  Speaking about sleep... I think I slept for 10 hours.  I guess it helped me clear my head.  

Well last weekend was Parent's Weekend.  My parents came around noon on Saturday.  I showed them around campus and I think my dad was really impressed by the campus and school... I don't know why he was impressed now.  I've been here for more than a month.  And he's seen the campus about four times.  But it was fun being able to see and hang out with my family.  Well, last week was probably one of my best weeks here.  After finishing my two tests last Wednesday, the weekend basically started for me.  My Hall and I started playing Madden 2003 a lot and we've been having tournaments basically all night.  It's funny how much trash talking we do.  Well Kyle our RA got us hooked on Knockout 2002.  It's such a sweet game... so we started talking about boxing tournaments... both on PS2 and in real life.    So yeah... Brian preformed at TDU friday night.  It was pretty cool, we played football before his big performance.  Two drunk guys joined in on the game... it was funny.  

Well I am not looking forward to the end of this week.  I have a test on Thursday in GBUS and gotta do my speech in GCOM on Friday.  Got to work on my programming assignment in CS... blah I don't like work =P I want to be lazy.  Well I hope all the UVA people enjoyed their fall break.  Well I guess I should return to my work...the weekend needs to be here...

Well I'm home for the weekend. My house seems really different... I love the feel of carpet and not having to worry about wearing scandals in the shower. And the internet is a lot faster than JMU's struggling network. It felt kinda weird coming home, I guess it didn't take long for me to get used to college and college life. But now since I'm home, it's cool. My sister keeps saying that I've changed... I don't know what she's talking about. This week went by really fast. I'm starting to enjoy all my classes, so the academic factor of college is getting better. Even though the week went by fast, it was sad and depressing. I'm sorry about Jacob. I didn't know Jacob that well, but I had the pleasure of meeting him. He was a great guy. Originally, I was coming back home for Alice's Birthday. But after the accident, I also wanted to attend the service. Thanks Mike for driving Megan and I back home. So Mike got to campus around 1. I took him to festival for lunch mmm... Cranberry Farms... and all Mike did was critize JMU's campus... bastard. So while I was finishing up on my last class, he went to the mall. So, we got home around 6:30 and I went out to dinner with my family. We talked about a lot of things and I told them about college. We needed up at Price Club getting more stuff for college. I forgot/needed a lot of stuff. I still need a TV... hopefully I can get one before I go back. I'm not asking for much, just a TV for me to watch football and to play PS2. Speaking of football, I wish I could've been able to attend the JMU football game, oh well. Justin, Sarah, and Ed better be there! This weekend looks busy, hopefully I'll be able to hang out with everybody before I leave. Blah, I didn't know that it rained so much here. And since my dad's out of the country, nobody has been mowing the lawn. So my mom wants me to mow the thick lawn. Well, I don't know when's the next time I'm coming back. But if you guys are interested in visiting or seeing what's college like, give me a call or something. Well I'm off. I hope everyone is having fun at school and enjoying life. Take care and be safe. HAPPY BIRTHDAY ALICE Lifehouse CD... on the 17th...

Hmm... seven more days till I leave for college. It's very scary realizing summer is also over... and where did it all go? To tell you the truth, I do not know what to expect. I am glad to be able to make my own choices and create and build friendships. I am going to look forward in hanging out with everyone though. And no... I don't have everything ready for college =P My parents are going to visit me again on that Friday after I move in, and they'll bring stuff that I forgot. And I already got invited to an apartment party and set a day to come back home =P and I haven't even gotten to college yet. Well I got my dorm information a couple of weeks ago... and I don't have a roommate. After thinking and talking to people about it... there are a lot of advantages and disadvantages of not having a roommate. I think the thing that bothers me the most is being so far away from everyone... and not being able to experience the advantages of a roommate. So my first bill from JMU came a couple of days ago... I was really surprised to see it... My mom gave me a lecture earlier and it really made me think. She never realized how much college really costed... she has always heard parents complain about it, but never seen a bill. It was a good idea that my parents did the prepaid program or the bill would've been much larger. But my mom told me to really be serious with college and do well because it's costly. Hmm... sometimes I take money for regranted... Well my aunt, uncle, and cousin came last week. It was really nice to be able to have the house to myself for a couple of days. I really enjoyed the quiet house and the feeling of being independent. So my cousin ended up getting a townhouse near Mason, so she isn't living with us. But I think my mom is going to try and get her to come over as much as possible. It's been an interesting week... the Liu-Shyu Clan painted their garages... and we have a poopy green colored garage now... I saw a lot of movies... thank you Justin... the dirty latino. And just chilled a lot. I took my cousin to Mason today. Man the campus is a lot larger than I thought. I really don't like the speedbumps =P I couldn't really see them. Afterwards, I spent a couple of hours at the mall with Rita. It was a lot of fun... especially seeing all these guys check her out =P I'm going to miss you a lot Rita! Good luck and have fun at India. I really like the friendship necklaces that we got. So... I have racquetball with the dirty latino and our TV dinner party to look forward to this week. I hope everything is going well with everyone... I'm going to miss all of you guys. And I don't know how I'm going to handle not seeing my family at college... It's crazy to think that we've completed high school and now we're going into something totally new and different. As you can see... I've been thinking a lot... I've been thinking way too much... But good luck to everyone... enjoy life!

It's kinda scary how my sister keeps saying that there's 32 more days of summer left.  For me, it's going to be even less.  I've really enjoyed this summer, even though I haven't been doing much.  I've really enjoyed relaxing and not worrying about stuff.  This past week, I've been hanging out with friends alot.  It's been a lot of fun, especially the car rides with Justin.  And of course, seeing my BEST FRIEND =P  I finally quit work today.  Now I can really enjoy my summer... even though I have to go to JMU on the 21st... which doesn't give me a lot of time.  Time really flew by, I remember counting down the weeks till I quit.  And now it's here, I'm happy.  I really liked what one of my bosses told me as I left today.  I have a lot of respect for him now.  He said that I've been a person that has had a profound impact on the company.  Both of my bosses told me to keep in touch and said I could work while I was in college.  I'm probably not goin to do that... but my parents keeps saying that I could go back next summer if I don't have a job.  I hope that doesn't happen, I wanna work for a new and bigger company.  But I've learned a lot and gained a lot of experience from these past 17 months that I've worked there.  I was really surprised how well I knew the software too.  (PDASecure... Ed...? =P)

Justin and I finally completed a goal that we've set for a long time now.  We stole a traffic barrel.  I was goin to keep it at my house, but my parents found out and totally freaked.  So I gave it to Justin to keep... 

IHOP was fun today.  It made me realize that I'm not totally ready for college and time is closing down.  I hope I can finish the jmu book by the 21st.  So I've been playing a lot of counterstrike lately.  I'm ranked 39 out of 200 people.  Haha I play way too much...  But I really enjoy some of the people who play on the server... I wanna see if I could out rank Mike, since I have a lot of free time to play.  Well my cousin is coming on Monday.  She's coming from Taiwan and she's going to attend Mason.  We still don't know if shes going to live near the campus or at my house.  I guess that'll be interesting... even though I won't be home after the year.  So my family is going on a tour next week.  That leaves the whole house  all to me for a couple of days.  I'm really going to enjoy it.  This LJ post has not been constant... sorry for talking about random things.  Well I hope everyone is having a great summer... I hope I can hang out with everyone.  I'm going to make the best out of this last month.  Later
